object:
本課程的設計希望幫助學生在修完本課程後可以：
一、對於後殖民理論有廣泛的了解;
二、以當代亞洲後殖民情狀的在場來分析其城市;
三、對於亞洲的社會性、文化政治與歷史脈絡有基本的概念;
四、對於歷史作為一個學門與再現過程有基本的概念;
五、對後殖民、建築、視覺文化與歷史書寫的專業用語有初步的認識;
六、經由課程的專題討論熟悉研究結果發表的技巧與應對。
On completion of this subject, students will be able to:
1. Demonstrate a broad understanding of the postcolonial theory;
2. Analyse Asian cities in terms of the presence of their postcoloniality;
3. Demonstrate an understanding of the social, cultural-political and historical context of Asia;
4. Demonstrate an understanding of history as a discipline and as a process of representation;
5. Use and understand postcolonial, architectural, visual-cultural and historiographical terminology;
6. Present synopses of thematic research findings to postgraduate standard.

core:
1.籌劃與執行專案研究之能力。
2.創新思考及獨立解決問題之能力。
3.國際視野及外語應用之能力。
1. an ability to plan and execute research projects;
2. an ability to innovative thinking and to solve problem independently;
3. an international vision and an ability to fluently use multi-languages.

grading:
Midterm presentation 20%;
Final Project 50%;
Homework 30%.

content:
The course covers the following topics: 
1. Overview of quantitative research methods; 
2. Descriptive and inferential statistics for analyzing data gathered from quantitative research designs;
3. The fundamentals and application of inferential statistics, including sampling techniques, data collection, data analysis, as well as data interpretation and presentation;
4. Univariate and bivariate analysis (e.g., correlation, t-test, ANOVA, simple regression) using the SPSS statistical software;
5. Writing of quantitative research papers.

note:
Prerequisites: at least one of the following courses taken before.
1. Financial Management;
2. Investment related courses;
3. Economics related courses; or
4. Accounting related courses.

